5. Proposed Training Framework

5.1 Composite Loss Function

UMVIS is trained end-to-end with a composite loss:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{total}} = \alpha_1 \mathcal{L}_{\text{text}} + \alpha_2 \mathcal{L}_{\text{speech}} + \alpha_3 \mathcal{L}_{\text{align}} + \alpha_4 \mathcal{L}_{\text{prosody}} + \alpha_5 \mathcal{L}_{\text{CMI}} + \alpha_6 \mathcal{L}_{\text{orth}} + \alpha_7 \mathcal{L}_{\text{anchor}} + \alpha_8 \mathcal{L}_{\text{contract}} + \alpha_9 \mathcal{L}_{\text{predict}}

The coefficients are set based on preliminary scaling analysis: \alpha_1 = 1.0, \alpha_2 = 1.0, \alpha_3 = 0.5, \alpha_4 = 0.3, \alpha_5 = 0.1, \alpha_6 = 0.05, \alpha_7 = 0.2, \alpha_8 = 0.01, \alpha_9 = 0.5.

5.2 Reconstruction Losses

Text Loss. Standard CTC loss for sequence-to-sequence alignment:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{text}} = -\log p_{\text{ctc}}(\mathbf{y} \mid \mathbf{Z}_c)

Speech Loss. Multi-domain reconstruction loss:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{speech}} = \lambda_{\text{mel}} \|\mathbf{x}_{\text{mel}} - \hat{\mathbf{x}}_{\text{mel}}\|_1 + \lambda_{\text{stft}} \|\text{STFT}(\mathbf{x}) - \text{STFT}(\hat{\mathbf{x}})\|_2^2 + \lambda_{\text{wave}} \|\mathbf{x}_{\text{wave}} - \hat{\mathbf{x}}_{\text{wave}}\|_1

5.3 Differentiable Temporal Alignment

We employ Soft-DTW (Cuturi and Blondel, 2017) to align latent sequences with text tokens:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{align}} = \text{Soft-DTW}_\gamma(\mathbf{Z}_c, \mathbf{H}_{\text{text}})

where \gamma is the smoothing parameter controlling the soft-min approximation. Additionally, we apply InfoNCE (van den Oord et al., 2018) to maximize mutual information between aligned segments:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{InfoNCE}} = -\log \frac{\exp(\text{sim}(\mathbf{z}_i, \mathbf{h}_i) / \tau)}{\sum_j \exp(\text{sim}(\mathbf{z}_i, \mathbf{h}_j) / \tau)}

5.4 Prosodic Fidelity Loss

Supervision on extracted prosodic features:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{prosody}} = \lambda_{F_0} \|F_0 - \hat{F}_0\|_1 + \lambda_{\text{energy}} \|E - \hat{E}\|_2^2 + \lambda_{\text{vad}} \text{BCE}(\text{VAD}, \hat{\text{VAD}})

5.5 Conditional Mutual Information Minimization

We minimize I_{\text{CLUB}}(\mathbf{Z}_p; \mathbf{Z}_s \mid \mathbf{Z}_c) using the conditional CLUB estimator described in Section 3.5. The variational network q_\psi is implemented as a 3-layer MLP taking concatenated [\mathbf{Z}_p, \mathbf{Z}_c] and outputting parameters of a Gaussian distribution over \mathbf{Z}_s.

5.6 Orthogonality Penalty

As defined in Section 3.4:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{orth}} = \sum_{i \neq j} \left| \frac{\mathbf{Z}_i^T \mathbf{Z}_j}{\|\mathbf{Z}_i\|_2 \|\mathbf{Z}_j\|_2} \right|^2

5.7 Anchor Synchronization Loss

MSE between projected content and prosody latents at forced-aligned phoneme boundaries:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{anchor}} = \sum_{k \in \text{boundaries}} \left\| \text{MLP}_c(\mathbf{Z}_c(t_k)) - \text{MLP}_p(\mathbf{Z}_p(t_k)) \right\|_2^2

5.8 Contractive SSM Penalty

Soft penalty encouraging \|\bar{\mathbf{A}}(t)\|_2 \leq 1 - \delta:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{contract}} = \frac{1}{T} \sum_{t=1}^T \max(0, \|\bar{\mathbf{A}}(t)\|_2 - (1 - \delta))^2

5.9 Predictive Head Loss

MSE between predicted future latent state \hat{\mathbf{Z}}(t+\tau) and actual future state:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{predict}} = \frac{1}{T-\tau} \sum_{t=1}^{T-\tau} \|\mathbf{Z}(t+\tau) - \hat{\mathbf{Z}}(t+\tau)\|_2^2

