Appendix F: Streaming Scheduler Algorithm

F.1 Full Streaming Inference with Predictive Caching

```
Algorithm 4: UMVIS Streaming Inference Scheduler

Constants:
    CHUNK_SIZE_MS = 20          # Audio chunk duration
    PREDICTION_HORIZON_MS = 300 # Lookahead for prediction
    CACHE_CONFIDENCE_THRESH = 0.7

State:
    mode ∈ {LISTENING, SPEAKING}
    Z_current                 # Current latent state
    audio_buffer              # Accumulated user audio
    transcript_partial        # Incremental ASR output
    pred_cache                # Queue of (speech_chunk, confidence)
    turn_boundary_detector    # VAD + turn-taking model

Initialize:
    Z_current = ZeroState()
    mode = LISTENING

while conversation_active:
    if mode == LISTENING:
        # Receive audio chunk
        chunk = microphone.read(CHUNK_SIZE_MS)
        audio_buffer.append(chunk)
        
        # Update latent state
        u_t = SpeechEncoder(chunk)
        Z_current = SSM_Step(Z_current, u_t)
        
        # Update partial transcript
        transcript_partial = CTC_Decode_Stream(Z_current.c)
        
        # Predictive pre-computation
        if len(transcript_partial) > min_tokens_for_prediction:
            Z_future = Predictor(Z_current, transcript_partial)
            
            # Decode future speech
            future_speech_chunks = []
            for tau_offset in [100, 200, 300]:  # ms
                Z_at_tau = PredictorAtOffset(Z_current, transcript_partial, tau_offset)
                speech_chunk = SpeechDecoder_Stream(Z_at_tau)
                future_speech_chunks.append((tau_offset, speech_chunk))
            
            # Compute confidence scores (e.g., based on prediction uncertainty)
            confidence = ComputePredictionConfidence(Z_future, transcript_partial)
            
            if confidence > CACHE_CONFIDENCE_THRESH:
                pred_cache.add(future_speech_chunks, confidence)
        
        # Check for turn boundary
        if turn_boundary_detector(audio_buffer):
            mode = SPEAKING
            Z_current = LatentStateReset(target_speaker, transcript_partial)
            
    elif mode == SPEAKING:
        # Determine response text (from LLM or scripted)
        response_text = GetNextResponseToken()
        
        if pred_cache.has_data() and ResponseMatchesPrediction(response_text):
            # Use precomputed cache
            output_audio = pred_cache.pop_first()
        else:
            # Fallback: generate on-the-fly
            u_t = TextEncoder(response_text)
            Z_current = SSM_Step(Z_current, u_t)
            output_audio = SpeechDecoder_Stream(Z_current)
        
        speaker.play(output_audio)
        
        if ResponseComplete():
            mode = LISTENING
            pred_cache.clear()
            audio_buffer.clear()
```

