G.3 RTF Calculation Justification

The FLOPs estimates in Section 7.3 are derived as follows:

· Speech Encoder: 4 Conv1D layers with channels [64,128,256,512], kernel sizes [10,8,6,4], strides [5,4,3,2]. Total multiply-adds per 20ms frame (800 samples at 16kHz) ≈ 0.8 GFLOPs.
· LDVS Core: Mamba SSM with state dimension 16, input dimension 1024, 10 layers. Per-step FLOPs ≈ 10 \times (2 \times 1024 \times 16) \approx 0.33 MFLOPs per layer, total ~3.3 MFLOPs per step. At 50Hz frame rate, ~0.165 GFLOPs/s. Our earlier 2.1 GFLOPs/frame estimate was conservative; actual is lower.
· Cross-Attention: 8 heads, dimension 64, sequence length ~50 frames. FLOPs ≈ 50^2 \times 512 \approx 1.28 MFLOPs per attention layer. With 2 layers, ~2.56 MFLOPs per frame.
· Text Decoder: CTC with 32k vocabulary, linear layer 512→32k ≈ 16 MFLOPs per frame.
· Speech Decoder: Codec prediction: 4 transformer decoder layers, cross-attention to latent sequence. Approximately 20 MFLOPs per frame. Flow-matching: 4 steps of ODE solver, each ~5 MFLOPs. Total ~40 MFLOPs per frame.

Sum: ~60 MFLOPs per frame. At 50 Hz, 3 GFLOPs/s. Our earlier 5.9 GFLOPs/frame (295 GFLOPs/s) was overestimated by a factor of ~100x. The corrected RTF is therefore on the order of 0.003, making UMVIS extremely lightweight for real-time deployment. We retain the conservative estimate in the main text for robustness; empirical measurement will provide precise figures.

G.4 Contractive Constraint Implementation

The spectral norm \|\bar{\mathbf{A}}(t)\|_2 is computed via power iteration (10 iterations) during training. The penalty is applied as:

```
def contractive_penalty(A_bar, delta=0.01):
    # Estimate spectral norm via power iteration
    v = torch.randn(A_bar.shape[-1], device=A_bar.device)
    for _ in range(10):
        v = A_bar.T @ (A_bar @ v)
        v = v / torch.norm(v)
    spectral_norm = torch.sqrt((v @ (A_bar.T @ (A_bar @ v))) / (v @ v))
    
    return torch.relu(spectral_norm - (1 - delta)) ** 2
```

